    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ThrowingPredicateN
extends AbstractThrowingPredicateN<AbstractThrowingPredicateN.Handler,ThrowingPredicateN>
    Represents a predicate that accepts n arguments and produces a boolean-valued result or throws a throwable. This is the predicate specialization for ThrowingToBooleanFunctionN. All boolean-producing predicates are derived from this n-arity specialization. This is the throwing variation of PredicateN.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is AbstractThrowingPredicateN.testAllUnchecked(Object...).

    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    ThrowingToBooleanFunctionN, PredicateN
